I-Assisted Legal Education focuses on designing and deploying intelligent procedural literacy systems that make complex court processes understandable and accessible to the public.

Procedural Justice Innovation aims to translate legal rules into transparent, repeatable formats that promote fairness, accountability, and equal access to courts.

Open-Source System Design involves building and maintaining collaborative ecosystems on platforms like Notion, GitHub, and Substack, enabling community contribution and continuous public improvement.

Pro Se Litigation Strategy is about structuring real filings and teaching modules that empower self-represented litigants to navigate judicial systems confidently and effectively.

